      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title fw-bold">Custom Two-Pass Assembler (C)</h2>
        <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-3 text-muted">Systems Programming & Architecture</h6>
        <p class="card-text">
          Designed and implemented a full assembler that converts assembly language into machine code. 
          This project involved low-level memory manipulation, symbol table management, and two-pass logical parsing.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-light p-3 rounded mb-3">
          <h5 class="small fw-bold">Key Technical Challenges:</h5>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Memory Efficiency:</strong> Implementing manual memory allocation and dynamic structures in C.</li>
            <li><strong>Bitwise Logic:</strong> Handling machine code instructions via bit manipulation and binary encoding.</li>
            <li><strong>Two-Pass Parsing:</strong> Resolving forward references and managing a complex symbol table architecture.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
